A critical section is a piece of code where shared data is accessed.

Only one thread should execute this area at a time.

ASCII

        Thread A
            |
            V
    +----------------+
    | Critical Area  |
    +----------------+
            ^
            |
        Thread B

Both must not enter together.

Multiple CPUs and multiple kernel threads may access the same memory at the
same time.

Without protection:

    CPU0 ---> modify data
    CPU1 ---> modify data

Result:
    Corruption
    Wrong values
    Kernel crash


